JEANETTA MENNINGER; WIDOW OF FAMED DOCTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeanetta Lyle Menninger, 93, a journalist and widow of the late Dr. Karl 
Menninger. Mrs. Menninger was principal of the preparatory school at Central 
College for Women in Lexington, Mo., in 1923-26. She left education to pursue a 
career in journalism, first as a reporter for the Utica, N.Y., Daily Press.In 
1930, Mrs. Menninger joined the public relations staff at Columbia University, 
and in 1932 moved to Topeka to assist Menninger -- who died in 1990 -- in 
writing a monthly column for the Ladies Home Journal. In 1936, she became 
editor of the Bulletin of the Menninger Clinic, a position she held until she 
retired in 1970, except for the three years she lived in Los Angeles (1938-41). 
In Topeka, Kan. on Wednesday. 
