<TEXT>
<P>
 Dr. David D. Michaels, 69, leading ophthalmologist who taught at UCLA's Jules 
Stein Eye Institute. He lectured and wrote widely, contributing articles to the 
American Journal of Ophthalmology and other professional journals.His book, 
"Visual Optics & Refraction -- A Clinical Approach," was popular in advanced 
study programs. Michaels earned bachelor's and master's degrees in psychology 
from Illinois Institute of Technology, a bachelor's in physics and chemistry 
from Roosevelt University in Chicago, and a bachelor's and doctorate in 
medicine from the University of Illinois at Chicago. He maintained a private 
practice in San Pedro for more than three decades and chaired the ophthalmology 
department at San Pedro Peninsula Hospital. He was also on staff at UCLA, Bay 
Harbor, Torrance Memorial and Long Beach Memorial hospitals and Harbor UCLA 
Medical Center. Michaels also taught at Northwestern, Loyola of Chicago and 
Roosevelt universities. Off duty, Michaels was an artist, specializing in oil 
painting and award-winning miniature military figurines. On Nov. 13 in Los 
Angeles of cancer. 
