<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; NEWSPAPER GROUP NAMES NEW EDITOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Albuquerque Tribune Editor Timothy J. Gallagher has been named editor of the 
Ventura County Star group of newspapers, company officials said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gallagher, 38, will replace John R. Irby, who abruptly resigned late last week 
citing "philosophical differences" with the company's management. 
</P>
<P>
 Editor of the Tribune since 1987, Gallagher will take control of the 
newspapers Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Gallagher's hiring and Irby's resignation are the latest in a series of 
management changes in the Ventura County newspaper group, which is owned by 
Ohio-based Scripps Howard newspapers. Gallagher has been a Scripps journalist 
for 17 years. 
</P>
<P>
 The group's daily newspapers have undergone several changes since publisher 
John P. Wilcox arrived last year. Coverage of local news has been shifted to 
pages deeper inside the main section, the price of home delivery has been 
increased and, late last month, the Star-Free Press and its editions changed 
their names to the Star. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley and Thousand Oaks papers have also added Star to their 
mastheads. J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
