<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL; NO. 12 MINNESOTA IMPROVES TO 6-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Townsend Orr scored 13 of his 17 points in the first half to lead 12th-ranked 
Minnesota to a 90-65 victory over Rhode Island on Sunday at Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
 Orr scored 11 points in the final 12:36 of the first half as the Golden 
Gophers (6-0) rolled to a 51-27 halftime lead in their first game since Dec. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Rhode Island (3-2) scored 13 consecutive points early in the second half to 
close to within 59-47 with 12:43 to play before Orr made a layup to start a 
10-2 run. 
</P>
<P>
 Seton Hall 99, Nevada Las Vegas 79 -- Donnell Williams, who sat out last 
season because of a foot injury, scored 21 points to lead the Pirates (4-2) 
over the Rebels (0-2) at East Rutherford, N.J. 
</P>
