<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NBA; PORTLAND BEATS SACRAMENTO AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rod Strickland scored 24 points, including a driving layup with 36 seconds to 
play, as the Portland Trail Blazers extended their home winning streak against 
the Sacramento Kings to 22 games Sunday night with a 93-88 victory at Portland. 
</P>
<P>
 Strickland's layup came off a give-and-go with Clyde Drexler and gave Portland 
a 92-88 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Kings missed three shots on their next possession and Drexler added a free 
throw to give Portland its third consecutive victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss ended a four-game winning streak for the Kings, their longest since 
1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The Kings have not won in Portland since January 1986. 
</P>
</TEXT>
