<P>
ANTON LEADS WAY FOR USC WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jody Anton scored 20 points and Karleen Shields added 16 Sunday, leading the 
24th-ranked USC women's basketball team past Stephen F. Austin, 81-76. 
</P>
<P>
 USC (5-1) trailed, 32-30, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Anton made an 18-footer with 9:23 left to give USC the lead for good. Stephen 
F. Austin (3-3) pulled to 74-73 with 3:22 left on a layup by Latonio Bonnett, 
but came no closer. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonnett finished with a team-high 18 points and eight rebounds. 
