<HEADLINE>
<P>
BANKRUPTCY COVERAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While Orange County tries to hold off creditors with its record-high municipal 
bankruptcy filing, county taxpayers get no respite from today's 5 p.m. deadline 
for paying the first installment of their property taxes. Despite having to pay 
up at the treasurer-tax collector's office, the center of nationwide attention 
due to the county's massive losses in the securities market, taxpayers are 
taking some comfort in knowing that their checks are being placed in a 
separate, low-risk fund. A28 
</P>
<P>
 Additional stories, pictures, graphics: A28, A29 
</P>
