<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: BUENA PARK; FAMILY AND AUTHORITIES SEEK TIPS IN 
HIT-AND-RUN DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A residents' group is spreading flyers to collect information about a 
hit-and-run driver who killed a local teen-ager. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Pugh, 18, was killed instantly at about 5:30 p.m. last Tuesday 
when his motorcycle was struck by a red pickup truck at Alondra Boulevard and 
Stage Road in nearby La Mirada, said Lt. Daryl Lance of the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 About 50 friends and residents are trying to find eyewitnesses to the 
accident, family friend Jennifer Patalsky said. They plan to have 3,000 to 
4,000 flyers distributed by early this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Friends are also seeking donations for a trust fund to help the family pay for 
the funeral and to offer a reward to witnesses, Patalsky said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're begging the public for information," she said. "We have nothing to go 
on." 
</P>
<P>
 David Pugh, the father of the victim, said the family has drawn tremendous 
emotional support from the effort. 
</P>
<P>
 "Having people call and ask to help is helping me, not bothering me," he said 
from his Huntington Beach home. "I want the person who did this to my son to be 
caught. My baby was only 18 years old, and he was left there to die. It's just 
not human." Christopher was buried Saturday in Norwalk. 
</P>
<P>
 People with information should call the Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Department in Norwalk at (714) 994-2970. Donations can be made to the Chris 
Pugh Trust Fund at any Wells Fargo Bank. LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
