drove with three friends, Santa Ana Police Sgt. Anthony Levatino said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mondragon's friends immediately drove him to a Santa Ana hospital emergency 
room and he was later transferred to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he 
later died, Levatino said.  
</P>
<P>
 Police say they don't have a motive for the shooting, which took place at 2:20 
a.m. near 1500 W. Edinger Ave. It is being investigated by the department's 
gang unit. Levatino said investigators do not know if the shooter was passing 
in another car or was on foot. 
