<P>
MAKING IT IN O.C.; DISC MAKER PLANS EXPANSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Disc Manufacturing Inc. plant in Anaheim makes audio compact discs as well 
as CD-ROMs and multimedia discs for Apple Computer, 3DO, Broderbund and other 
computer companies.Early next year, the company plans to move from its 
30,000-square-foot plant to a 220,000-square-foot facility, which was acquired 
recently in Anaheim from Rockwell International. Disc Manufacturing, which is 
owned by Chicago-based Quixote Corp., has about 190 employees in Orange County. 
