<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: COLDWELL BANKER UNIT GETS NEW EXECUTIVE VICE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Larry Romito has been promoted to executive vice president-general sales 
manager for Coldwell Banker Residential Brokerage, a unit of Mission 
Viejo-based Coldwell Banker Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Romith previously served as senior vice president and chief administrative 
officer of the firm. 
</P>
<P>
 In his new position, Romito will be responsible for sales and operations of 
the more than 300 company-owned offices in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Arthur C. Darrow has been named chief executive of Dames & Moore, an 
international engineering and environmental consulting firm, effective Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Darrow, 51, succeeds George D. Leal who will continue as chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 Darrow, who has been with the Los Angeles-based company 21 years, is currently 
president and chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
 He will retain the title of president. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 David T. Blankenhorn was named executive vice president-branch administration 
of California State Bank in West Covina. 
</P>
<P>
 Most recently, Blankenhorn was president and chief executive of Bank of 
Newport in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Leslie A. Koll has joined Jenny Craig Inc. as senior vice president, 
marketing. 
</P>
<P>
 Prior to joining the Del Mar-based weight management company, Koll was 
managing partner for the Los Angeles office of Pelletier, Koll Weill, a 
business development and marketing consulting firm. 
</P>
