<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 500th Restaurant: Boston Chicken, the rapidly-growing restaurant franchise 
that jumped into the Southern California fast food market in July, will open 
its 500th franchise store in the nation in Brea today. The restaurant, which 
specializes in roasted chicken similar to fare offered by the likes of El Pollo 
Loco and Kentucky Fried Chicken, will be a franchise location operated by 
Boston Pacific, a subsidiary of CKE Restaurants, the Anaheim-based parent 
company of the Carl's Jr. chain, which has had its own competitive troubles in 
the Southland market. Boston Pacific has franchise rights to develop about 300 
new Boston Chicken restaurants in Southern California during the next five 
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
