</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ameritech Tries to Sell Plan to Justice Department: Attempting to win an 
endorsement from federal antitrust enforcers, Ameritech Corp. has offered to 
temporarily scale back its plan to get into the long-distance business, 
proposing a limited trial in the Chicago area, an executive said.If approved by 
a federal judge, Ameritech would be the first regional Bell company to provide 
long-distance service, an experiment that would cover roughly 8 million people 
and be closely watched by other Bells that are clamoring to get a piece of the 
$60-billion-a-year business. Ameritech wants the Department of Justice to back 
its plan before the court. The department is reviewing the plan and appeared 
receptive, Ameritech General Counsel Tom Hester said. 
</P>
