<P>
 GM Cuts 30,000 Vehicles From Production Forecast: Affecting fourth-quarter 
production in North America, the reduction was larger than many Wall Street 
observers expected and prompted analysts to trim their earnings estimates for 
the giant auto maker and predict more difficult times ahead for General Motors 
Corp. GM stock lost 37.5 cents per share Friday, closing at $37 1/4 on the New 
York Stock Exchange. Since September, GM's stock has fallen by more than a 
quarter amid growing concern about the auto maker's ability to cash in on the 
current auto sales boom. 
</P>
