BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PUC Sets Date for Decision on Electric Deregulation: The California Public 
Utilities Commission has adopted a new schedule for restructuring the state's 
electric utility industry, an attempt to lower power bills in the state.The PUC 
had earlier expected to settle on a new regulatory structure in 1994, with a 
competitive market for the largest power users to begin Jan. 1, 1996. But since 
last April, various plans have been debated in a lengthy series of commission 
hearings. The PUC now plans to issue a revised proposal on March 22, 1995, with 
final adoption in September. The commissioners left a start date undecided, but 
few observers now expect deregulation to begin by January, 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
