<TEXT>
<P>
 More People Working but Jobless Rate Is Up: Australian employment increased by 
30,400 in November to a record 8.03 million people in the work force, the 
Bureau of Statistics reported, but more people looking for work nudged up the 
unemployment rate to 9.3%, from 9.1% in October. 
</P>
