PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 November Industrial Output Jumps 23.6%: Chinese industries produced goods 
worth $17.6 billion in November, up 23.6% over the year-ago period, the State 
Statistics Office reports. The November expansion of industrial production 
compared with the 24.3% year-on-year growth rate recorded for October. Total 
output in the first 11 months of the year was up 17.9% over the same period for 
1993, the bureau said. 
</P>
