<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; RWANDA; MASSACRE WITNESSES SLAIN, OFFICIAL SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Witnesses of genocide attacks on minority Tutsis in Rwanda are being singled 
out for execution by extremist Hutus in refugee camps in southwest Rwanda, a 
U.N. spokesman said in Kigali, the capital. Capt. Stephane Grenier said 
violence had increased in the camps in that area. "People have been killed with 
machetes and in grenade attacks," he added. U.N. officials said the slayings 
appeared to be the work of gangs from the former Rwandan army, which was ousted 
by the Rwandan Patriotic Front in July, and members of the Hutu militia known 
as the Interahamwe who were responsible for the attacks on Tutsis. 
