<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN MISSING 8 DAYS AT BIG SUR IS FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A San Rafael man who disappeared after going for a walk at the Esalen 
Institute eight days ago was found in a hollowed-out tree trunk where he had 
taken refuge. 
</P>
<P>
 Two bloodhounds fixed on David Leon Holt's scent when they were brought into 
the search Saturday and tracked him down in about two hours, said their owner, 
Maury Tripp of Santa Cruz. 
</P>
<P>
 Holt, 48, was suffering from frostbite on his left foot, hypothermia and other 
complaints. He was hospitalized in serious but stable condition Sunday night, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Holt was last seen packing his car Dec. 2. He decided to take one last walk 
that afternoon before dinner and never returned. 
</P>
<P>
 Holt told Tripp that he found himself in a steep canyon as darkness fell. He 
tried to take a shortcut back to the institute but fell and hurt himself and 
could not walk. 
</P>
<P>
 He spent the next eight days sheltered in the tree trunk to keep dry from the 
rain, and crawled to a stream every day to drink, Tripp said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
